      "widgets_values": [
        "ℹ️ S-16 Selective Color — tighten a hue band and extract its saturation mask\n\nChain: LoadImage → N-15 Hue/Saturation per Range (hue_center=0 red band, band_width=30°, sat_mult=1.3) → PreviewImage. In parallel, the same input also feeds N-16 Saturation Mask Builder (sat_min=0.3, sat_max=1.0, feather=0.1) so the workflow demonstrates both selective-color primitives introduced in batch-6.\n\nTypical use: isolate reds / yellows / greens by hue, push or pull saturation only inside that band, then reuse the N-16 mask downstream for ImageBlend, luminosity-restricted grades, or mask-aware retouch nodes.\n\nNote: N-16 outputs a MASK and is intentionally left unconsumed here to keep the demo pack-core-only. Wire it into any downstream blend / mask consumer in your own graph."
